condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Sched 2 B 4 (b) | Description :Establish District Planning Committees in each district | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Sched 2 B 4 (c) | Description :Establishment of Provincial Planning Team comprising of representatives of linedepartments | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Sched 2 Section 1 A (a) | Description :Establish and maintain throughout the implementation of the project aProject Steering Committee with representatives from the Recipient at the national and provincial levels | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Sched. 2 B 4 (a) | Description :Establish District Planning Teams in each district of Khammouane Province forthe duration of the project | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Sched. 2 Section F, 1 (b) | Description :Ensure environmental screening of subprojects and civil works and ifneeded, full EIA and EMP to be carried out and prepared | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Sched. 2, Section F, 1 (a) | Description :Ensure all subproject are viable and designed/ appraised with regardto public health, safety, social and environmental standards acceptable to the Assoc and accdg to Env.&Soc. Safeguard Framework |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Sched. 2, Section F, 1 (c and d) | Description :Ensure social screening of subprojects and civil works and asneeded carry out RAP, IPDPs accdg to Env/Social Safeguard Framework | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section D, para 2 (a) | Description :the Recipient shall:Maintain and cause the Province tomaintain, throughout the period of implementation of the Project, the component management unit established for implementing Part Cof the Project, provided with sufficient resources and competent staff in adequate numbers and with appropriate terms of reference,in each case satisfactory to the Association; | Frequency :Monthly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section D, para 2 (b) | Description :Cause the Province to provide, throughout the period ofimplementation of the Project, the PAFO and the DAFO, with sufficient resources and competent staff in adequate numbers and withappropriate terms of reference, in each case satisfactory to the Association. | Frequency :Monthly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section D, para. 3 | Description :For purposes of providing ALGs and the AEGs under the Project, theRecipient shall apply the proceeds of the Financing allocated toCategories (1)(b) and (6) to finance Sub-projects in accordancewith the guidelines, procedures and criteria set forth in the Operational Manual, and the additional terms and conditions set forthin subsection I.E of this Schedule. | Frequency :Monthly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section D, para. 4 | Description :The Recipient shall ensure that the Province disclose adequateinformation on grants to the ALG Eligible Villages and Eligible Agriculture Entrepreneurs. | Frequency :Monthly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section E, para. 1 | Description :No Sub-project shall be eligible for financing out of the proceedsof the Financing unless the corresponding proposals for the Sub-projects have been prepared and submitted, and the review ofproposals and award of the Sub-grants have been undertaken, in accordance with the guidelines, procedures and selection criteriaset forth in the Operational Manual. | Frequency :Monthly
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section E, para. 2 | Description :No Sub-grant shall be made to finance expenditures pertaining toor involving negative items stipulated in the FA. | Frequency :Monthly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section E, para. 3 | Description :Subprojects under BBG shall follow the criteria stipulated in theFA and be carried out according to the operational manual. | Frequency :Monthly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section E, para. 6 | Description :Sub-grants under the PDF may be provided to provincial departmentsto support investments which may include: the expansion of teacher training facilities, improvements to the provincial agricultureextension services center, and other small-scale infrastructure improvements expected to cost up to the Kip equivalent of fiftythousand United States dollars (US$50,000) per Sub-project. | Frequency :Monthly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section E, para. 7 | Description :With respect to each eligible Sub-project for which the Recipienthas decided to make available a Sub-grant, the Recipient shall enter into or cause to be entered into a Sub-grant Agreement withtheproposed Beneficiary on terms and conditions approved by the Association, and stipulated in the FA | Frequency :Monthly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section E, para. 8 | Description :No Sub-project shall be eligible for financing out of the proceedsof DDF, ALG, AEG or PDF unless a Sub-grant Agreement has been concluded to this effect on terms and conditions set forth in thisSub-section E and the Operational Manual. | Frequency :Monthly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section E, para. 9 | Description :The Beneficiary shall exercise its rights under each Sub-grantAgreement in such manner as to protect the interests of the Recipient and the Association and to accomplish the purposes of theFinancing. Except as the Association shall otherwise agree, the Beneficiary shall not assign, amend, abrogate or waive anySub-grant Agreement or any of its provisions. | Frequency :Monthly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section E, paras. 4 and 5 | Description :Subprojects under ALG and AEG shall follow the criteriastipulated in the FA and be carried out according to the operational manual. | Frequency :Monthly
Finance Agreement :Section V 1 (a) | Description :Agreement with NTPC regarding the Tha Thot Irrigation Scheme and DownstreamIrrigation | Due Date :31-Dec-2008
